},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Moreover, remember that there was a “Done” list in my weekly board? That also does something\nspecial. I have a BFT link that, whenever clicked, does the following:","position":{"start":{"line":100,"column":1},"end":{"line":100,"column":1}},"key":"Y1PaRaCyqy"}],"key":"Fd9WsD2YtX"},{"type":"list","ordered":false,"spread":false,"position":{"start":{"line":103,"column":1},"end":{"line":107,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":103,"column":1},"end":{"line":103,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Loop through every card in the “Done” list","position":{"start":{"line":103,"column":1},"end":{"line":103,"column":1}},"key":"Z6pIqJ3NqI"}],"key":"t2KIrku7Jl"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":104,"column":1},"end":{"line":104,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"For each card, find the Board ID that represents the board the card came from","position":{"start":{"line":104,"column":1},"end":{"line":104,"column":1}},"key":"MMfd7vXva6"}],"key":"WcRcL056en"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":105,"column":1},"end":{"line":107,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Move the card to that board, put it in a “Done” list that is automatically created using the\nnumber of the current active week.","position":{"start":{"line":105,"column":1},"end":{"line":105,"column":1}},"key":"hNJ35vaCSS"}],"key":"gmr3OKN06u"}],"key":"UESffhXZgF"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":108,"column":1},"end":{"line":108,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"So, the general flow of cards through this system looks like this:","position":{"start":{"line":108,"column":1},"end":{"line":108,"column":1}},"key":"TllLXgbUiJ"}],"key":"qtREtfRA06"},{"type":"list","ordered":true,"start":1,"spread":false,"position":{"start":{"line":110,"column":1},"end":{"line":120,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":110,"column":1},"end":{"line":110,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Create cards in a project board that represent things to be done.","position":{"start":{"line":110,"column":1},"end":{"line":110,"column":1}},"key":"WgVJYaavr2"}],"key":"XS50tjan8q"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":111,"column":1},"end":{"line":111,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"When it’s time to work on a task, move it to the “Doing” list","position":{"start":{"line":111,"column":1},"end":{"line":111,"column":1}},"key":"tmodIvbmTx"}],"key":"AS8EYiCYhv"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":112,"column":1},"end":{"line":112,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"BFT moves that card to my “Weekly” board, to a list w/ the project name","position":{"start":{"line":112,"column":1},"end":{"line":112,"column":1}},"key":"HwNnFWpXV6"}],"key":"MjGWNP6MH6"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":113,"column":1},"end":{"line":114,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"This happens at the beginning of the week, along with an estimation of the time needed for\neach card.","position":{"start":{"line":113,"column":1},"end":{"line":113,"column":1}},"key":"fJsOYh0KNU"}],"key":"RmJzCex5FV"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":115,"column":1},"end":{"line":115,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"As the week progresses, I mark off the hours that I’ve spent on each card.","position":{"start":{"line":115,"column":1},"end":{"line":115,"column":1}},"key":"uWG0I8zZzU"}],"key":"rvAO7anQnG"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":116,"column":1},"end":{"line":116,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"When the card’s hours remaining reaches 0, I move it to the “Done” list","position":{"start":{"line":116,"column":1},"end":{"line":116,"column":1}},"key":"mWuIPuOzx4"}],"key":"wNgQaZeCDH"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":117,"column":1},"end":{"line":118,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"At the end of the week, I click my “board cleanup” link, and it returns each card to its\noriginal project board.","position":{"start":{"line":117,"column":1},"end":{"line":117,"column":1}},"key":"oImSexcdNK"}],"key":"e7FJDEP8LH"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":119,"column":1},"end":{"line":120,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Next week, I repeat this cycle.","position":{"start":{"line":119,"column":1},"end":{"line":119,"column":1}},"key":"ESGekiLetw"}],"key":"fb8sQR0L4I"}],"key":"AmuY6YFAJA"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":121,"column":1},"end":{"line":123,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"And that’s about it - I’ve found that this process is a nice way to keep both a high-level\nview of what needs to be done for my various projects (on each project board). It also allows\nmy to dig into specific to-do items throughout the week (on my weekly board).","position":{"start":{"line":121,"column":1},"end":{"line":121,"column":1}},"key":"oPsd1HPvuQ"}],"key":"E1A7njUgAW"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":125,"column":1},"end":{"line":126,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I’d love to hear feedback and thoughts about how other people manage their time throughout\nthe week! Hopefully some of you all find this useful.","position":{"start":{"line":125,"column":1},"end":{"line":125,"column":1}},"key":"cfxN6gKxkM"}],"key":"pnjEBtzYhQ"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":128,"column":1},"end":{"line":128,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Extras","position":{"start":{"line":128,"column":1},"end":{"line":128,"column":1}},"key":"xU25FnboJY"}],"identifier":"extras","label":"Extras","html_id":"extras","implicit":true,"key":"b0FgYCuBQe"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":130,"column":1},"end":{"line":131,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Butler for Trello commands can be a little bit difficult to compose. Below I’ll post the\ntwo main commands that I use to handle all the card-moving described above.","position":{"start":{"line":130,"column":1},"end":{"line":130,"column":1}},"key":"PWtb7p3esX"}],"key":"n5OYVP87ll"},{"type":"heading","depth":3,"position":{"start":{"line":133,"column":1},"end":{"line":133,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The weekly board","position":{"start":{"line":133,"column":1},"end":{"line":133,"column":1}},"key":"MseaNj1fl6"}],"identifier":"the-weekly-board","label":"The weekly board","html_id":"the-weekly-board","implicit":true,"key":"i9XtdNy8mM"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":135,"column":1},"end":{"line":136,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The weekly board has a “butler” list where the command is defined in a card (that’s how\nyou define board-specific BFT commands). Here’s the command:","position":{"start":{"line":135,"column":1},"end":{"line":135,"column":1}},"key":"v8Od3bwKDe"}],"key":"Z0FLSVQDxa"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":138,"column":1},"end":{"line":138,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"{% raw %}","position":{"start":{"line":138,"column":1},"end":{"line":138,"column":1}},"key":"PA7qgrPLNT"}],"key":"K4ea9UGMxo"},{"type":"code","lang":"","value":"script: for each card in list \"Return\", remove all labels and move the card to list \"Returned | Week {weeknumber}\" on board \"{{%homeboard}}\" and move list \"Returned | Week {weeknumber}\" on board \"{{%homeboard}}\" to position 1 and clear custom field \"homeboard\"","position":{"start":{"line":139,"column":1},"end":{"line":141,"column":1}},"key":"JbrdZrQZgE"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":142,"column":1},"end":{"line":142,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"{% endraw %}","position":{"start":{"line":142,"column":1},"end":{"line":142,"column":1}},"key":"MT5to39Xsw"}],"key":"z1rc103zT9"},{"type":"heading","depth":3,"position":{"start":{"line":144,"column":1},"end":{"line":144,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"A global command for project boards","position":{"start":{"line":144,"column":1},"end":{"line":144,"column":1}},"key":"spwrqFq1kg"}],"identifier":"a-global-command-for-project-boards","label":"A global command for project boards","html_id":"a-global-command-for-project-boards","implicit":true,"key":"FpvqRdEocH"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":146,"column":1},"end":{"line":147,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I also use a global BFT command that moves the cards from each project board to the weekly\nboard when the card is moved to the “Doing” category.","position":{"start":{"line":146,"column":1},"end":{"line":146,"column":1}},"key":"FiHynK0zUM"}],"key":"dNlquNPhBn"},{"type":"code","lang":"","value":"when a card is added to list \"Doing\" by me, set custom field \"homeboard\" to \"{boardlink}\" and move the card to the top of list \"{boardname}\" on board \"Active\" and move list \"{boardname}\" on board \"Active\" to position 2","position":{"start":{"line":149,"column":1},"end":{"line":151,"column":1}},"key":"kOlxnGqnSA"}],"key":"YT4qMnTejT"}],"key":"yRF0BfkmPU"},"references":{"cite":{"order":[],"data":{}}},"footer":{"navigation":{"prev":{"title":"Introducing makeitpop, a tool to perceptually warp your data!\"","url":"/blog/2018/makeitpop","group":"2018"},"next":{"title":"I like Rust’s governance structure","url":"/blog/2018/rust-governance","group":"2018"}}},"domain":"http://localhost:3000"}